        {
          "ts": 3600,
          "value": null
        },
        {
          "ts": 7200,
          "value": "50"
        },
        {
          "ts": 10800,
          "value": "75"
        },
        {
          "ts": 14400,
          "value": "37.5"
        },
        {
          "ts": 18000,
          "value": "68.75"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "rsi_wilder_broken_chain_never_recovers",
      "primitive": "rsi_wilder",
      "params": {
        "period": 2
      },
      "description": "The seed (ts=7200) only needs the first 2 deltas and is unaffected by a later gap. ts=10800's value is itself missing, which breaks the Wilder recursion irrecoverably: every later frame stays missing even though ts=14400/18000 carry valid raw values, because avg[t] is a strict function of avg[t-1].",
      "input": [
